The '''Military Secrets Act''' was passed by the [[New Republic Senate/Legends|New Republic Senate]] during the [[Yuuzhan Vong War]]. It allowed the [[Chief of State (New Republic)/Legends|Chief of State]] to "declare a majority" of the Senate if a military council voted to approve a measure, thus avoiding the security compromise of a full vote.

